Phase 2.3.5 prose review for the Image feature guide is complete. The revised document and review report have been saved to `cache/generation/drafts/image-reviewed.md`.

**Key changes made:**
1. Added backticks around `ImageView` and `AnimatedImageView` in overview for API naming consistency
2. Added "(default)" annotation to `Image::ReleasePolicy::DETACHED`
3. Added default fitting mode clarification (`FILL` is default)
4. Added information about additional sampling modes (`BOX`, `BOX_THEN_NEAREST`, etc.)
5. Expanded AnimatedImageView description to mention WebP support and URL array animation
6. Added new "Frame Sequence from URL Array" subsection with `SetResourceUrls()`, `SetBatchSize()`, `SetCacheSize()`, and `SetFrameDelay()` examples
7. Added explanation of masking modes (`MASKING_ON_RENDERING` vs `MASKING_ON_LOADING`)
8. Clarified that N-patch borders are available only on `ImageView`

All code blocks were verified against public headers (`image-view.h`, `animated-image-view.h`, `image-enumerations.h`) and sample files. The guide uses typed setters (preferred idiom) rather than property-based APIs.
